"CONSTRUCTION OF LINE NEAR KING'S CROSS. Street Station, the City terminus, blossomed forth into a great banquetting room, gaily flaunting the banners of all nations, and at the feast Mr. Robert Lowe, a famous Chancellor of the Exchequer, suggested that Mr. Fowler, the engineer, should be christened Admiral of the Fleet. As the trains came in, one after the other, the City Police Band played triumphant airs, and the guests alighted proudly as though conscious that they were assisting at the birth of a new epoch in London transport. As, indeed, they were."